@page "/mud/project/sponsor"

<DocsPage MaxWidth="MaxWidth.Large" DisplayFooter="true">
    <DocsPageHeader Title="Sponsors & Backers" SubTitle="The continued development and maintenance of MudBlazor is secured by our sponsors" />
    <DocsPageContent>
        
        <DocsPageSection>
            <SectionHeader Title="Sponsor">
                <Description>
                    MudBlazor is open-source becuse we want to include the community in the project and to have influence over what direction we are heading. While MudBlazor is completely free to use, and always will be, we do have alot of contributors and a core team that invests alot of time into the project.<br/><br/>
                    We want to make sure MudBlazor becomes a financially stable project, and that is the reason we have gone with the crowd-funding concept, so that we can invest into infrastructure, possible dev payouts and potentially full time devs in the future.<br/><br/>
                    By supporting us you help secure the continued development and maintenance of MudBlazor, that bugs get fixed, new features gets implemented, support for coming versions of .NET and Blazor.
                </Description>
            </SectionHeader>
            
            <MudButton DisableElevation="true" StartIcon="@Icons.Custom.Brands.GitHub" Variant="Variant.Filled" Size="Size.Large" Class="docs-no-text-transform" Link="https://github.com/sponsors/MudBlazor" Target="_blank">Sponsor on GitHub</MudButton>
            <MudButton DisableElevation="true" StartIcon="@Icons.Filled.DataUsage" IconColor="Color.Info" Size="Size.Large" Variant="Variant.Filled" Class="docs-no-text-transform mx-2" Link="https://opencollective.com/mudblazor" Target="_blank">Sponsor on Open Collective</MudButton>
            
            <SectionSubGroups>
                
                <DocsPageSection>
                    <SectionHeader Title="What we do">
                        <Description>
                            <div class="d-flex flex-column px-2">
                                <MudBadge Class="mt-1" Color="Color.Primary" Dot="true" Origin="Origin.CenterLeft">
                                    <div class="pl-4 docs-line-height-normal">
                                       Oversee the library as a whole
                                    </div>
                                </MudBadge>
                                <MudBadge Class="mt-1" Color="Color.Primary" Dot="true" Origin="Origin.CenterLeft">
                                    <div class="pl-4 docs-line-height-normal">
                                        Planning features and decide which ones should be implemented and which should not
                                    </div>
                                </MudBadge>
                                <MudBadge Class="mt-1" Color="Color.Primary" Dot="true" Origin="Origin.CenterLeft">
                                    <div class="pl-4 docs-line-height-normal">
                                        Develop new features and ideas
                                    </div>
                                </MudBadge>
                                <MudBadge Class="mt-1" Color="Color.Primary" Dot="true" Origin="Origin.CenterLeft">
                                    <div class="pl-4 docs-line-height-normal">
                                        Fix reported bugs
                                    </div>
                                </MudBadge>
                                <MudBadge Class="mt-1" Color="Color.Primary" Dot="true" Origin="Origin.CenterLeft">
                                    <div class="pl-4 docs-line-height-normal">
                                        Write new documentation and improve on old
                                    </div>
                                </MudBadge>
                                <MudBadge Class="mt-1" Color="Color.Primary" Dot="true" Origin="Origin.CenterLeft">
                                    <div class="pl-4 docs-line-height-normal">
                                        Adopt new versions of .NET and Blazor
                                    </div>
                                </MudBadge>
                                <MudBadge Class="mt-1" Color="Color.Primary" Dot="true" Origin="Origin.CenterLeft">
                                    <div class="pl-4 docs-line-height-normal">
                                        QA, creating tests or manually testing
                                    </div>
                                </MudBadge>
                                <MudBadge Class="mt-1" Color="Color.Primary" Dot="true" Origin="Origin.CenterLeft">
                                    <div class="pl-4 docs-line-height-normal">
                                       Manage Issues/Feature Requests/Discussions/Pull Requests/Reviews on GitHub
                                    </div>
                                </MudBadge>
                                <MudBadge Class="mt-1" Color="Color.Primary" Dot="true" Origin="Origin.CenterLeft">
                                    <div class="pl-4 docs-line-height-normal">
                                        CI/CD workflows to ensure continuous delivery/deployment
                                    </div>
                                </MudBadge>
                                <MudBadge Class="mt-1" Color="Color.Primary" Dot="true" Origin="Origin.CenterLeft">
                                    <div class="pl-4 docs-line-height-normal">
                                        Community building e.g., Reddit, Twitter, Stack Overflow, Discord
                                    </div>
                                </MudBadge>
                            </div>
                        </Description>
                    </SectionHeader>
                </DocsPageSection>
                

                <DocsPageSection>
                    <SectionHeader Title="Where does the money go?">
                        <Description>
                            All funds are going to <CodeInline>Gardnet AB</CodeInline> which is a Swedish company owned by <MudLink Href="https://github.com/Garderoben">Garderoben</MudLink>, the creator of MudBlazor.<br/><br/>
                            <CodeInline>Gardnet AB</CodeInline> is using the funds to:
                            <div class="d-flex flex-column px-2">
                                <MudBadge Class="mt-1" Color="Color.Primary" Dot="true" Origin="Origin.CenterLeft">
                                    <div class="pl-4 docs-line-height-normal">
                                        Secure MudBlazor's future as the best choice out there.
                                    </div>
                                </MudBadge>
                                <MudBadge Class="mt-1" Color="Color.Primary" Dot="true" Origin="Origin.CenterLeft">
                                    <div class="pl-4 docs-line-height-normal">
                                        Cover expenses related to development of MudBlazor, e.g., domain names, certificates, hosting and licenses.
                                    </div>
                                </MudBadge>
                            </div>
                        </Description>
                    </SectionHeader>
                </DocsPageSection>

                <DocsPageSection>
                    <SectionHeader Title="What's the difference between GitHub and OpenCollective?">
                        <Description>
                            Funds received via <b>GitHub</b>, directly go to <CodeInline>Gardnet AB</CodeInline> and the core team's mission, the company is a profit entity with one goal, secure MudBlazor's future.<br/><br/>
                            Funds received via <b>Open Collective</b> are managed transparently and aimed to sustain MudBlazor and its needs.<br/>
                            As a <MudTooltip Text="A Fiscal Host is an entity that holds the money on behalf of a Collective, and takes care of accounting, taxes and invoices." Arrow="true" Placement="Placement.Top">Fiscal Host</MudTooltip> all funds are keept their until we submit a expense.
                        </Description>
                    </SectionHeader>
                </DocsPageSection>

            </SectionSubGroups>
